Jerome Boateng wants Bayern Munich to put their surprise defeat by Borussia Monchengladbach behind them when they visit Borussia Dortmund after the international break.

Pep Guardiola's side lost 2-0 at home to Monchengladbach on Sunday but remain 10 points clear at the top of the Bundesliga.

And Boateng, who will link up with Germany for a friendly with Australia and Euro 2016 qualifier with Georgia over the next week, wants to see a positive reaction in Bayern's next league game. 

